      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not about being \"fair\" though. it's about the reality. people don't just \"understand\" when their partner wastes years of their life and their security on a massive mistake. the shame is permanent. it's like, every time i look in the mirror, i just see a fraud. honestly, sometimes it feels like the only way to actually stop the weight and the embarrassment from existing is to just... stop being a part of it. to just make it all go away so no one has to deal with the wreckage anymore.",
